  				<tr>
  					<td align=center valign="top" width=100%><br>
  						<!--#beginContent#-->
  						<table align='center' cellpadding=5 width='85%'>  <tr><td class='spti2' width='100%'>PLAYER STRATEGY - NECROMANCER</td></tr>  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><font class='dbti'>NEVER UNDERESTIMATE THE POWER OF SHADOW STEP</font> - <small>Acadan, Tallon Zek</td></tr>
  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><p>Many thing that the true power of the PvP monsters wizzards and necros lies in their ability to root or snare you.But<br>
by around level 25 or so most if not everyone will resist magic based spells since most resistance items are MR<br>
and everyone wants MR the most cuz being rooted as a melleer means your death.  So keeping this in mind. NEVER mess&nbsp;<br>
around with casting darkness past 20 against melleers its useless your just wasting mana.  Instead the greatest thing&nbsp;<br>
you could possible do is Shadow step,DOT;shadowstep, DOT; Shadow step, DOT;  then start in with lifetaps if you have lost&nbsp;<br>
any health other wise just do your best to stay away from the person you are fighting if they are a melleer.<br>
Recast DOTs and lifetap as necessary.<br>
Now for casters. Fighting melleers is all pretty much the same against all six mellee based classes.  But when fighting casters&nbsp;<br>
you must have a different strategy for each class.<br>
First wizards<br>
With a wizard I definatly recomend sticking with your taps.  Dont waste time moveing around CHAIN TAP. Send your pet in after&nbsp;<br>
them and cast your taps as fast as possible dont mess around with DOTs because it takes so long for them to work its a waste of mana.<br>
<br>
Now for chanters<br>
close to the same for wizards however you have to fear their pet first and do your absolute best to keep your pet on them interupting them<br>
as much as possible.<br>
<br>
Mages.&nbsp;<br>
Probly the easiest class to beat because they lack any root or stun to keep you pet off of them.  I personally never cast on the mage<br>
I just fear their pet then send my pet after them.  At level 34 my pet will eat a mage alive, killing the mage in less than a minute.  just fear pet&nbsp;<br>
send your pet after the mage and follow the mages pet around and keep it feared.  Possibly throwing in a VoS or boil blood on the mage in case&nbsp;<br>
they zone while running from your pet.<br>
<br>
Druids&nbsp;<br>
The most important thing you can possibely remember to do to a druid is cast cancel magic on them to get rid of their SOW.  Sow is the main&nbsp;<br>
advantage druids and shaman have against you, soooo GET RID OF IT.  Then DOT and send your pet on them chain tapping as necessary.<br>
<br>
Clerics<br>
The only problem with clerics that you will ever have is them rooting your pet and healing themselves until you run out of mana.
'But they will<br>
run out of mana too' you might think.  That is partly true but trust me their heals are much more mana efficent than your taps and DOTs so you WILL<br>
run outa mana before they do. At least at level 34 cant remeber at newbie levels for sure.  Then after you run outa mana they will melee you to death.<br>
The best thing I recomend for clerics is to cast screaming terror on them after they root your pet. ST is a mez spell so it will hold them still until the<br>
root wears off on your pet and the pet can proced to woop their ass.  Again DOT then lifetap if needed<br>
<br>
Shaman.&nbsp;<br>
Ahhhhh the shaman.  What can I say. At level 34 and up (when they get a pet) they are some tuff mo fo's to beat.  However hardly imposible.&nbsp;<br>
First of all dont try to root the pet cuz root is more easily resisted then fear and they most certainly have given their pets an MR buff.  So fear their<br>
pet and then just as you did to the druids DISPELL THEIR SOW.  Let me repeat myself DISPELL THEIR SOW.  This is takening away a huge advantage they<br>
have over you.  Hell since their buffs are so damn good cast dispell 3 or 4 times and get rid of all them buffs they are a pain in the ass.  In between the dispells&nbsp;<br>
since dispell has a short refresh time cast your DOTs and do anything you can to keep your pet on them and not on their pet(BTW that counts for all pet classes)&nbsp;<br>
You will most certainly be DOTed with scourge and envenomed breath (which can kill you outright if you dont lifetap them) so keep your lifetaps up<br>
constantly giving yourself more HPs.<br>
<br>
Bards&nbsp;<br>
i left these guys for last cuz they can be the easiest class to fight or the hardest its just highly depends on the bards personal skill and if he twists the<br>
right songs.  Most likely they will sing a snareing song on you and bellow and also twist selos into that, or possibly just bellow and selos.  Remember bellow&nbsp;<br>
interupts your casting so you have to cast in between the beats of the song.  DOT them and constantly lifetap in between the beats of the song bellow.&nbsp;<br>
Cross your fingers and hope the bard isnt good at twisting songs.<br>
<br>
<br>
Well thats about all i can say so if you are ever on Tallon zek I generally hang around in the wurm groups or Crystal caverns so look me up.
<br>
<br>
<br>
</p></td></tr>
